rComments: John speaks softly but he definitely has a sense of humor. I also don't think he's very harsh on essay assignments. As long as the rubrics are followed, there's no reason you shouldn't do well on writing assignments. Textbook readings are also helpful but not totally required. The syllabus does say that students who read the book do better, though.
It will make you lose your interest in Abnormal Psychology. He speaks in monotone, and so lectures are extremely boring. He also grades very harshly on essay assignments.
